Citations
Date: 0/0/1863
Source: AJHR
Author:
Vol / Page: D6/18
Edition:
Quote: Many ... who held river claims worked very successfully by wing-dams, consisting of bags of sand laid into the strream, so as to cut off a portion of its bed, which, being drained by pumping, was paddocked out and passed through the cradle.
Notes: (Pyke Goldfields Reports)

Date: 0/0/1873
Source: Wild Will Enderby
Author: PYKE
Vol / Page: 18
Edition:
Quote: The Dunstan gold workings were of two kinds - technically known as `beach claims' and `bank claims' ... The former were on the sandy margins of the river, and were often extended by means of `wing-dams' and other ingenious devices far into the rushing waters.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1874
