Edition:
Quote: They built a wing-dam, ... them stakes is the remains of it - and they did get splendid gold.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1976
Source: Clyde on the Dunstan
Author: VEITCH
Vol / Page: 30
Edition:
Quote: Many favoured a `wing dam' when working in very shallow beaches. Bags filled with earth formed a 12 feet by 20 feet square. The water enclosed in this square was then baled or pumped out and the area worked dry.
Notes:

